The paper deals with the complexity of predicate logics, which is a topic that falls under the area of logic (cs.LO). The use of team semantics in the predicate logics also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The complexity analysis of the problems in the paper involves techniques from computational complexity theory, which is a subfield of computer science (cs.DS). The paper also deals with the satisfiability and validity problems, which are fundamental problems in computer science (cs.CC). Finally, the analysis of the Bernays-Schönfinkel-Ramsey prefix classes suggests a connection to mathematical logic and proof theory (cs.LG).
